
Concept used by David Armano, in Business Week at
http://www.businessweek.com/innovate/content/apr2007/id20070409_372598.htm


=Summary=

"*  Participating in conversations is not about crowdsourcing, it's about crowdmanaging
    
* Marketing is about facilitation, not about communication
    
* We designers should stop talking and start designing conversations. We should convert from marketers and information architects to conversation architects. Information is a one-way street, conversation isn't.
    
* Why is Twitter so hyped? Why all the fuss? I believe it's because Twitter has evolved from a simple service that initially allowed users to express mundane thoughts into a robust "conversation ecosystem."
(http://i-wisdom.typepad.com/iwisdom/2007/04/its_the_convers.html)



